            <section class="prose max-w-none">
              <h2>What is Gratuity?</h2>
              <p>
                Gratuity is a statutory monetary benefit paid by an employer to an employee for rendering services for a continuous period of five years or more. It is a form of gratitude for the employee's service to the company. In India, this is governed by the <strong>Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972</strong>.
              </p>

              <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Service Requirement:</strong> Minimum 5 years of continuous service.</li>
                <li><strong>Establishment:</strong> Any factory, mine, oilfield, plantation, port, railway company, or shop/establishment with 10 or more employees.</li>
                <li><strong>Exception:</strong> In case of <strong>death or disablement</strong>, the 5-year rule is waived.</li>
              </ul>

              <h2>Gratuity Formula & Calculation</h2>
              <p>The calculation depends on whether your company is covered under the Payment of Gratuity Act.</p>

              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="comparison-table">
                  <thead>
                    <tr>
                      <th class="w-1/3">Parameter</th>
                      <th class="w-1/3">Covered under Act</th>
                      <th class="w-1/3">Not Covered under Act</th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr>
                      <td><strong>Basis of Salary</strong></td>
                      <td>Basic Salary + DA</td>
                      <td>Basic Salary + DA</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td><strong>Days per Year</strong></td>
                      <td>15 days</td>
                      <td>15 days</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td><strong>Days in Month</strong></td>
                      <td>26 working days</td>
                      <td>30 calendar days</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td><strong>Rounding Service</strong></td>
                      <td>&gt; 6 months rounded to 1 year</td>
                      <td>Fractions are generally ignored</td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>

              <h3>1. Employees Covered under the Act</h3>
              <p>The formula uses 26 working days a month:</p>
              <div class="formula-box">
                $$G = \frac{15 \times S_{last} \times Y}{26}$$
              </div>
              <p>Where:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>$G$ = Gratuity Amount</li>
                <li>$S_{last}$ = Last drawn Basic Salary + Dearness Allowance</li>
                <li>$Y$ = Completed years of service (rounded up if months > 6)</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>2. Employees Not Covered under the Act</h3>
              <p>The formula uses 30 calendar days a month:</p>
              <div class="formula-box">
                 $$G = \frac{15 \times S_{last} \times Y}{30}$$
              </div>
              <p>Note: Years of service are usually not rounded up. 7 years and 10 months is considered 7 years.</p>

              <h2>Tax Rules on Gratuity (AY 2025-26)</h2>
              <p>Gratuity tax treatment falls under "Income from Salaries".</p>
              <ol>
                <li><strong>Government Employees:</strong> Fully tax-exempt u/s 10(10)(i).</li>
                <li><strong>Private Employees (Covered):</strong> The least of the following is exempt:
                  <ul>
                    <li>Actual gratuity received.</li>
                    <li>₹ 20,00,000 (Statutory limit).</li>
                    <li>15 days salary based on last drawn salary for each year of service ($15/26 \times Salary \times Years$).</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>
